schema:
Table: member
Columns:
  - member_id: text (PRIMARY KEY) NOT NULL
  - first_name: text
  - last_name: text
  - email: text
  - join_date: text
  - graduation_year: integer
  - major: text
  - role: text
Sample Data (up to 5 rows):
  - member_id=rec123, first_name=John, last_name=Doe, email=john.doe@example.com, join_date=2019-09-01, graduation_year=2023, major=Computer Science, role=President
  - member_id=rec124, first_name=Jane, last_name=Smith, email=jane.smith@example.com, join_date=2019-09-01, graduation_year=2022, major=Biology, role=Vice President
  - member_id=rec125, first_name=Michael, last_name=Johnson, email=michael.j@example.com, join_date=2019-09-15, graduation_year=2024, major=Mathematics, role=Treasurer
  - member_id=rec126, first_name=FirstName0, last_name=LastName0, email=student0@example.com, join_date=2019-10-01, graduation_year=2023, major=Computer Science, role=Member
  - member_id=rec127, first_name=FirstName1, last_name=LastName1, email=student1@example.com, join_date=2019-10-01, graduation_year=2024, major=Biology, role=Member

Table: income
Columns:
  - income_id: text (PRIMARY KEY) NOT NULL
  - amount: integer
  - date_received: text
  - source: text
  - notes: text
  - link_to_member: text
Sample Data (up to 5 rows):
  - income_id=rec0s9ZrO15zhzUeE, amount=50, date_received=2019-10-17, source=Dues, notes=Member dues payment, link_to_member=rec123
  - income_id=rec7f5XMQZexgtQJo, amount=50, date_received=2019-09-04, source=Dues, notes=Member dues payment, link_to_member=rec124
  - income_id=rec8BUJa8GXUjiglg, amount=50, date_received=2019-10-08, source=Dues, notes=Member dues payment, link_to_member=rec125
  - income_id=rec8V9BPNIoewWt2z, amount=50, date_received=2019-10-02, source=Dues, notes=Member dues payment, link_to_member=rec126
  - income_id=recCRWMfFqifuKMc6, amount=50, date_received=2019-09-18, source=Dues, notes=Member dues payment, link_to_member=rec127

Table: event
Columns:
  - event_id: text (PRIMARY KEY) NOT NULL
  - event_name: text
  - event_date: text
  - location: text
  - description: text
  - budget: integer
Sample Data (up to 5 rows):
  - event_id=event1, event_name=Welcome Party, event_date=2019-09-05, location=Student Union, description=Welcome party for new members, budget=500
  - event_id=event2, event_name=Tech Workshop, event_date=2019-10-10, location=Engineering Building, description=Workshop on new technologies, budget=300
  - event_id=event3, event_name=End of Year Celebration, event_date=2019-12-15, location=Campus Center, description=Celebration for the end of the year, budget=800

Table: expense
Columns:
  - expense_id: text (PRIMARY KEY) NOT NULL
  - amount: integer
  - date_spent: text
  - vendor: text
  - description: text
  - event_id: text
Foreign Keys:
  - event_id -> event.event_id
Sample Data (up to 5 rows):
  - expense_id=exp1, amount=450, date_spent=2019-09-03, vendor=Party Supplies Inc, description=Supplies for welcome party, event_id=event1
  - expense_id=exp2, amount=200, date_spent=2019-10-08, vendor=Tech Store, description=Equipment for workshop, event_id=event2
  - expense_id=exp3, amount=750, date_spent=2019-12-10, vendor=Catering Company, description=Food for end of year celebration, event_id=event3

Table: budget
Columns:
  - budget_id: text (PRIMARY KEY) NOT NULL
  - semester: text
  - total_amount: integer
  - start_date: text
  - end_date: text
Sample Data (up to 5 rows):
  - budget_id=budget1, semester=Fall 2019, total_amount=5000, start_date=2019-09-01, end_date=2019-12-31
  - budget_id=budget2, semester=Spring 2020, total_amount=6000, start_date=2020-01-01, end_date=2020-05-31

Table: major
Columns:
  - major_id: text (PRIMARY KEY) NOT NULL
  - major_name: text
  - department: text
Sample Data (up to 5 rows):
  - major_id=major1, major_name=Computer Science, department=Engineering
  - major_id=major2, major_name=Biology, department=Sciences
  - major_id=major3, major_name=Mathematics, department=Sciences
  - major_id=major4, major_name=History, department=Humanities
  - major_id=major5, major_name=English, department=Humanities

Table: zip_code
Columns:
  - zip: text (PRIMARY KEY) NOT NULL
  - city: text
  - state: text
Sample Data (up to 5 rows):
  - zip=12345, city=Springfield, state=IL
  - zip=23456, city=Riverdale, state=NY
  - zip=34567, city=Sunnyville, state=CA
  - zip=45678, city=Laketown, state=MI
  - zip=56789, city=Mountainview, state=CO
